The paper discusses the concept of blameworthiness in strategic games, which is a topic closely related to game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the role of knowledge in determining blameworthiness, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents a logic that describes the interplay between knowledge and blameworthiness, which is a topic in mathematical logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the settings with imperfect information, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
